d’Avrohom{\highlight7 <ITC>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*3>}3{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}Not only is God’s compassionate providence concerned with the earth and enduring 
things, but His compassion and providence extend even to those creatures which are destined 
to perish.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Avudraham{\highlight7 <ITC>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*4>}4{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}God redeems those who are in captivity and saves others from being taken in captivity.\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*5>}5{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}The Sabbath, more than other days, lends itself to offering praise and thanksgiving to God. 
When man rests from his physical labor and is relieved of material concerns, his soul is free to 
pursue the intellectual and spiritual aspects of life. These pursuits lead him to serve God and to 
praise Him.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Radak{\highlight7 <ITC>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*6>}6{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}We will proclaim His kindliness in the morning of redemption. And while yet in the 
darkness of exile we proclaim our belief in His faithfulness.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Rashi{\highlight7 <ITC>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*7>}7{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}The Sabbath day of rest affords me the opportunity to observe and appreciate the greatness 
of Your work.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Radak{\highlight7 <ITC>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*8>}8{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}God’s ‘works’ are the visible creation, while His ‘thoughts’ are the Divine purpose behind 
each created thing.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Seporno{\highlight7 <ITC>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*9>}9{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}Others translate, ‘You have increased my might like that of the wild ram.’\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*10>}10{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}The palm and the cedar both enjoy a long life span and flourish during all seasons. Thus 
they symbolize the lasting happiness of the righteous in contrast to the short prosperity of the 
wicked.\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*11>}11{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}On the sixth day, the Levites sang Psalm 93, ‘Adonoy is King, He has clothed Himself in 
majesty,’ because He completed the work of creating and reigned over all His creatures.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Rosh 
Hashana{\highlight7 <ITC>} 31a\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*12>}12{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <IT>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}Psalms{\highlight7 <ITC>} 104:31.\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*13>}13{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <IT>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}Psalms{\highlight7 <ITC>} 113:24.{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*14>}14{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}God’s “Name” is the name spelled {\highlight7 <IT>}YudHeyVuvHey.{\highlight7 <ITC>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*15>}15{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}God’s “mention” is the name spelled {\highlight7 <IT>}AlefDaledNunYud.{\highlight7 <ITC>} In this world God’s name is 
only {\highlight7 <IT>}written{\highlight7 <ITC>} as {\highlight7 <IT>}YHVH{\highlight7 <ITC>} but is pronouced {\highlight7 <IT>}Adonoy.{\highlight7 <ITC>} In the future world, however, God’s Name will 
