{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*28>}28{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <IT>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}Psalms{\highlight7 <ITC>} 20:10.{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*29>}29{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}This verse referred to the Kohanim and the Levites who served (dwelt) in the Holy Temple 
(Your House); it is at all times applicable to scholars and devout men who study and pray in 
houses of worship and study.\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*30>}30{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <IT>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}Psalms{\highlight7 <ITC>} 84:5{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*31>}31{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <IT>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}Psalms{\highlight7 <ITC>} 144:15{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*32>}32{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}According to Rav S.R. Hirsch, David here declares, “I will dedicate myself to serve You and 
to fulfill Your will in loyal obedience,” for in serving God, man causes His Name to be blessed.\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*33>}33{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}Not simply {\highlight7 @hh}{\highlight7 <HEB>}\rtlch \'f0\'c4\'f4\'c0\'ec\'c0\'e0\'fa\'c6\'e9\'ea\'c8{\highlight7 {\ltrch @ee}}{\highlight7 {\ltrch<}{\ltrch ENG}{\ltrch>}}\ltrch Ða report of Your wondersÐbut {\highlight7 @hh}{\highlight7 <HEB>}\rtlch \'e3\'c4\'e1\'c0\'f8\'c5\'e9 \'f0\'c4\'f4\'c0\'ec\'c0\'e0\'fa\'c6\'e9\'ea\'c8{\highlight7 {\ltrch @ee}}{\highlight7 {\ltrch<}{\ltrch ENG}{\ltrch>}}\ltrch  the “words”Ðthe lessons 
that Your wonders teach.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}S.R. Hirsch{\highlight7 <ITC>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*34>}34{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}People in general will speak of God’s wondrous might in punishing the wicked (Sodom, 
Egypt, etc.) while David will proclaim that God’s greatness is measured more by His kindliness 
than by His awesomeness.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Siach Yitzchok{\highlight7 <ITC>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*35>}35{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}He is gracious in bestowing reward and merciful in punishment.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Siach Yitzchok{\highlight7 <ITC>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*36>}36{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}Your works which are the cause of your being thanked by sensitive people; similarly, cause 
your pious ones to bless You.Ðbased on {\highlight7 <IT>}S.R. Hirsch.{\highlight7 <ITC>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*37>}37{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}The penalties for transgressions are just, but God is gracious in the actual punishment 
inflicted on the sinner.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Siddur HaGra{\highlight7 <ITC>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*38>}38{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}He is near to all who call upon Him, but His nearness can be perceived {\highlight7 <IT>}only{\highlight7 <ITC>} by those who 
call upon Him in truth, who truly mean to have God enter into their lives.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}S.R. Hirsch{\highlight7 <ITC>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*39>}39{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}While God {\highlight7 <IT>}hears{\highlight7 <ITC>} all who cry unto Him in truth, He {\highlight7 <IT>}answers{\highlight7 <ITC>} those who fear Him, who 
subject their desires to His will.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Siach Yitzchok{\highlight7 <ITC>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*40>}40{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <IT>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}Psalms{\highlight7 <ITC>} 115:18. You should pause between {\highlight7 @hh}{\highlight7 <HEB>}\rtlch \'f2\'e5\'c9\'ec\'c8\'ed{\highlight7 {\ltrch @ee}}{\highlight7 {\ltrch<}{\ltrch ENG}{\ltrch>}}\ltrch  and {\highlight7 @hh}{\highlight7 <HEB>}\rtlch \'e4\'c7\'ec\'c0\'ec\'e5\'cc\'e9\'c8\'e4\'cc{\highlight7 {\ltrch @ee}}{\highlight7 {\ltrch<}{\ltrch ENG}{\ltrch>}}\ltrch . Similarly, in all the {\highlight7 <IT>}Psalms{\highlight7 <ITC>}, the 
word {\highlight7 @hh}{\highlight7 <HEB>}\rtlch \'e4\'c7\'ec\'c0\'ec\'e5\'cc\'e9\'c8\'e4\'cc {\highlight7 {\ltrch @ee}}{\highlight7 {\ltrch<}{\ltrch ENG}{\ltrch>}}\ltrch  is not connected to the preceding verse.\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*41>}41{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}According to the Sages, it is implied that one should not rely even on the merit of his 
sainted ancestors, the Patriarchs, for deliverance.\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*42>}42{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}Only the four cubits of ground which will receive him one day are {\highlight7 <IT>}his{\highlight7 <ITC>}; of all the world they 
are the one possession which is guaranteed to him.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}S.R. Hirsch{\highlight7 <ITC>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*43>}43{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}Jacob, more than anyone, sensed God’s nearness and protection throughout his difficult 
life and through all the trials to which he was subjected.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}S.R. Hirsch{\highlight7 <ITC>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*44>}44{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}He alone has always proven dependable and faithful, for there are no limits to His essence 
and to His power.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Ibn Ezra, Radak{\highlight7 <ITC>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*45>}45{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}Others render “their sorrows.” Both translations coexist! God not only heals their 
physical pains but also abbreviates their sorrows as well.\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*46>}46{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}Not one of the myriad stars was created accidentally; each has a unique purpose and 
function.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Siach Yitzchok{\highlight7 <ITC>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*47>}47{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}Each musical instrument has its unique function. In the times of King David, the harp was 
used to arouse those who slept. The psalmist may be indicating that the harp arouses the 
sleeping soul of man to recognition of the miraculous ways in which God shows His Divine 
Providence for us every day.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Siach Yitzchok{\highlight7 <ITC>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*48>}48{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}God does not delight in those who place their trust in the strength of horses or in their 
own strength.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Tzelosa d’Avrohom{\highlight7 <ITC>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*49>}49{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}The Psalmist addresses the dwellers in Jerusalem and Zion, not the city itself.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Tzelosa 
d’Avrohom{\highlight7 <ITC>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*50>}50{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}Israel is the receiver and preserver of God’s divine Law, the Torah, which includes {\highlight7 <IT>}chukim,{\highlight7 <ITC>} 
statutes which confine the physical, sensual aspects of man within the bounds of moral purity, 
and also {\highlight7 <IT>}mishpotim,{\highlight7 <ITC>} laws which govern communal life. Among the nations, law is determined 
by the views they hold at a given time and place concerning the needs of a society, and so their 
laws are based on expediency.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}S.R. Hirsch{\highlight7 <ITC>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*51>}51{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <IT>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}Genesis{\highlight7 <ITC>} 1:6±7 indicates that there are waters above the heavens.\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*52>}52{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}The heavenly bodies, unlike humans and earthly things, were created from materials that 
do not deteriorate.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Kuzari{\highlight7 <ITC>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*53>}53{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}None of the heavenly bodies transgresses the Divine decree about its functions in the role 
for which it was created. The sun never violates its mandate to serve by day or the moon by 
night. According to {\highlight7 <IT>}Ibn Ezra,{\highlight7 <ITC>} the verse might also be translated “He issued a decree which will 
not pass away,” for God’s {\highlight7 <IT>}decree{\highlight7 <ITC>} is permanent and immutable.\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*54>}54{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}Elders and youngsters praise God {\highlight7 <IT>}together{\highlight7 <ITC>} while the young men must be separated from 
the maidens. In the Temple separate facilities were erected for the women. So too must there be 
separate seating in our synagogues.\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*55>}55{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}The fulfillment of the last two verses will take place in the Messianic era.\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*56>}56{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}The old songs will not suffice to express the joy at the wonders in the Messianic 
future.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Radak{\highlight7 <ITC>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*57>}57{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <IT>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}Israel{\highlight7 <ITC>} is the nation as a whole, the {\highlight7 <IT>}children of Zion{\highlight7 <ITC>} are the elite of the people.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Seporno{\highlight7 <ITC>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*58>}58{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}Although God desires all His people, nevertheless, our ultimate salvation will come 
through the merit of His humble ones.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Rav Simcha Bunim of Pczyscha{\highlight7 <ITC>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*59>}59{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}One’s praise of God emanating from deep within him, (not mere lip service) becomes a 
